events.text:
Day Rock
Today is Rock Day I have decided.
It’s not because I’m going to collect any, but simply because I feel a certain solidity to my life.
The routine is easy; there are no external pressures.
All I have to do is collect the moon carrots and feed the moon bunny.
My jet pack has been especially helpful in my daily gathering.
I do wonder what it uses for fuel.
It never seems to run out, no matter how much I use it and I’ve never manually refilled it.
I suspect it accepts but one type of fuel: it is powered by my own natural gasses.
I do to toot quite often.
Too many carrots will do that.
Could it be my suit was designed to utilize this source of fuel?
I wonder who designed it.
Did they know about the moon carrots beforehand to design a suit completely powered by flatulence?
And if so, does that mean they know I’m still up here?
Will someone come and get me?
I await the day when I can get off this rock.
